text: Odor is a type of physical quality defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's molecules being aerially dispersed and perceived by an odorant receptor.

Spatial pattern is a type of morphology and is defined as a spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts. It is exactly synonymous with distribution and is also relatedly synonymous with pattern.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:qualitative rdfs:subClassOf :quality .
text: qualitative is a type of quality.
Deviation from normal is a type of qualitative, which is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

Amount is a type of qualitative data and it is defined as the number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism. It has exact synonyms such as presence or absence in an organism and quantitative. Additionally, amount has related synonyms including count in organism, number, and presence.

Amplitude is a type of physical quality of a process, defined as a physical quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the size of the bearer's maximum displacement from the 'normal' position, when periodic motion is taking place.

Sensitivity toward is a type of organismal quality, which is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation. Additionally, sensitivity toward has an exact synonym: sensitivity.
Size is a type of morphology and it is defined as a quality of morphology that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's physical magnitude.
Length is a type of 1-dimensional extent and it is defined as a 1-D extent quality, which is equal to the distance between two points.
Mass is a type of physical quality and it is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the proportion of the bearer's amount of matter.
Closure is a type of morphology and it is defined as a morphological quality pertaining to the degree to which an object contains an opening, aperture, orifice, or vent.

Position is a type of physical quality characterized by a spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity. It is exactly synonymous with location, placement, and relational spatial quality.

Structure is a type of morphology and is defined as a quality of morphology inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements, and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form. Moreover, structure has a broad synonym, conformation, and an exact synonym, relational structural quality.
Temperature is a type of physical quality with the definition of being the thermal energy of a system.

Texture is a type of morphology and it is defined as a morphologic quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative size, organization, and distribution of its surface elements or the representation or invention of the appearance of its surface; visual and tactile surface characteristics.
Rate is a type of physical quality of a process and it is defined as a quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.
Time is a type of physical quality and it is defined as a quality in which events occur in sequence.

Viability is a type of organismal quality that is defined by an organismal quality inhering in a bearer or a population. This is due to the bearer's disposition to survive and develop normally or the number of surviving individuals in a given population.

Increased speed is a type of speed and also a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a speed which is relatively high. Moreover, "high speed" is an exact synonym of increased speed, and "fast speed" is relatedly synonymous with it.

Decreased speed is categorized under types of speed and is also considered a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a speed which is relatively low. Furthermore, decreased speed has exact synonyms, which are "slow" and "slow speed."
Old is a type of age that carries the definition: an age which is relatively high.
Young is a type of age, and it has the definition of being an age which is relatively low.

Blue is a type of color that is defined as a color hue with a low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between green and indigo, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 490 nanometers.

White is a type of color that is defined as an achromatic color of maximum brightness; it is the color of objects that reflect nearly all light of all visible wavelengths. Additionally, white has a related synonym, whitish.

An irregular spatial pattern is a type of spatial pattern characterized by the lack of consistency in the magnitude of or the relationships between its repeated parts. This definition is ingrained in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's characteristics.
Colorless is a type of color pattern characterized by a color quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's lack of color. Additionally, it is related to the synonym unpigmented.
Down is a type of direction that is defined as a directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction from a higher to a lower point.

Left is a type of direction and it is defined as a directional quality that exists in a bearer due to the bearer's direction, which is akin to the direction of an object to the north when it is facing east.

Right is a type of direction and it is defined as a directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces west.
Up is a type of direction and it is defined as a directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction from a lower to a higher point.

Increased frequency is a type of frequency and is also known as a type of increased rate of occurrence. It is defined as a frequency which is relatively high. Moreover, "increased frequency" has an exact synonym, "high frequency", and a related synonym, "frequent".

Decreased frequency is categorized as a type of frequency and is also considered a type of decreased rate of occurrence. It is defined as a frequency which is relatively low. Moreover, decreased frequency is exactly synonymous with low frequency and is relatedly synonymous with infrequent.

Hard is a type of hardness and a type of increased object quality. It is defined as having a hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure. Additionally, hard is related to the synonyms firm, impenetrable, and tough.

Branched is a type of branchiness and it is defined as a branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having branches. Moreover, "branched" has exact synonyms which are "ramified" and "ramiform."

Coiled is a type of coiling and is defined as a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curled or wound, especially in concentric rings or spirals. It has an exact synonym, which is spiral. Additionally, coiled has related synonyms including helical, helicoid, helicoidal, and helix-shaped.
Curled is a type of shape that has the definition of being a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having parallel chains in undulate fashion on the border.

Curved is a type of curvature that is defined as a curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or being marked by a curve or smoothly rounded bend. Additionally, curved has a narrow synonym, bowing, and a related synonym, curled.

Flat is a type of flattened and it is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature. Additionally, flat has a related synonym, plate-like.

Circular is a type of elliptic, and it is defined as a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being such that every part of the surface or the circumference is equidistant from the center. Moreover, circular has related synonyms such as round and rounded.
Sporadic is a type of occurrence and is defined as a quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's once or in a few unpredictable instances.

Invariant is a type of variability characterized by a quality of variability that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's absence of or failure to exhibit variation. This definition of invariant aligns with its exact synonym, "uniform," and it is also closely associated with the related synonym "constant."
A regular spatial pattern is a specific type of spatial pattern characterized by a pattern quality that it possesses due to having a repeatable or predictable placement.
Present is a type of amount and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's existence. Additionally, it has a related synonym, "present in organism."
Increased length is a type of length and also a type of increased size. It is defined as a length quality which is relatively large. Additionally, increased length has the exact synonym "long."

Decreased length is a type of length and also a type of decreased size. It is defined as a length quality which is relatively small. Furthermore, "short" is an exact synonym for decreased length, while "shortened" and "stubby" are related synonyms.

Increased size is a type of size and also a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a size quality which is relatively high. Related synonyms for increased size include big, enlarged, expanded, great, and large.

Decreased size is characterized as a type of size and also falls under the category of decreased object quality. It is defined as a size quality which is relatively low. The term decreased size is closely synonymous with hypoplasia and underdeveloped, while it is relatedly synonymous with reduced, small, and tiny.

Increased thickness is a type of increased size and also falls under the category of thickness. It is defined as a thickness which is relatively high. The term increased thickness has exact synonyms including high thickness, stout, and thickened. Additionally, it has a related synonym, thick.

Decreased thickness is a type of decreased size and is also a type of thickness. It is defined as a thickness which is relatively low. Additionally, decreased thickness has an exact synonym, which is low thickness, and has related synonyms including slender and thin.

Increased volume is a type of increased size and a type of volume. It is defined as a volume which is relatively high. Furthermore, "increased volume" has the exact synonym "high volume" and a related synonym "large volume."

Decreased volume is a type of decreased size and also a type of volume. It is defined as a volume which is relatively low. Additionally, decreased volume has an exact synonym, low volume, and a related synonym, small volume.
Decreased width is a type of decreased size and also a type of width. It is defined as a width which is relatively small and has a related synonym, narrow.

Increased width is a type of increased size and also a type of width. It is defined as a width which is relatively large. Furthermore, increased width is related to the synonyms broad, wide, and wide/broad.

Closed is a type of closure and it is disjoint with open. It has a definition as a morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording blocked passage or view. Moreover, closed is related to the synonym blocked.
Closure incomplete is a type of open and is defined as a morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording not completed blocked passage or view.
Open is a type of closure and is defined as a morphological quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording unobstructed passage or view.
Bilateral is a type of position, defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two sides; it is two-sided.
Crowded is a type of position characterized by a positional quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's state of being overfilled.

Erect is a type of position and is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being upright in position or posture. Furthermore, "erect" has an exact synonym, "upright."
Misrouted is a type of position that is defined by a positional quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's having mistakenly taken a course, way, or passage, making it ill-routed.
Prostrate is a type of position and it is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being stretched out and lying at full length along the ground.
Unilateral is a type of spatial pattern that is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's involvement of only one part or side.

"Fused with" is a type of structure that possesses a structural quality by virtue of the bearer's being merged with another entity. It is exactly synonymous with "fused" and "fused to", and is relatedly synonymous with "coalesced", "joined with", and "merged with".

Continuous is a type of occurrence and is defined as a quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being uninterrupted in time, sequence, substance, or extent. Additionally, continuous has an exact synonym: uninterrupted.

Discontinuous is a type of occurrence characterized by a quality of a single process that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by breaks or interruptions. It has "interrupted" as an exact synonym and is also relatedly synonymous with "intermittent."
Smooth is a type of texture and it is defined as a texture quality that exists in an object due to the object having a surface that is free from roughness or irregularities.
A decreased rate is a type of rate and also a type of decreased process quality. It is defined as a rate which is relatively low and has an exact synonym, "slow rate."

Increased rate is a type of rate and also a type of increased process quality. It is defined as a rate which is relatively high. Moreover, increased rate has exact synonyms, including fast rate and high rate.
Thickness is a type of 1-D extent and is defined as a 1-D extent quality which is equal to the dimension through an object as opposed to its length or width.
Volume is a type of 3D extent and it is defined as a 3D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

Width is a type of 1-D extent and has a definition as a 1-D extent quality, which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to the opposite side. Additionally, width is related to the synonym breadth.
Oblong is a type of 2D shape characterized by a shape quality that it possesses due to having a somewhat elongated form with approximately parallel sides.

Elliptic, a type of superelliptic, is defined by a spheroid quality that is inherent in a bearer due to the bearer's oval shape with two axes of symmetry, as produced by a conical section. It is exactly synonymous with ellipse-shaped, ellipsoid, and elliptical. Additionally, elliptic is relatedly synonymous with oval and ovoid.
Brown is a type of color with the definition of being a color consisting of dark orange, red, of very low intensity.
Opacity is a type of optical quality that is defined by the ability of the bearer to absorb visible light.

Opaque is a type of opacity and is defined as an optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being clear; it does not transmit or reflect light or radiant energy. Additionally, opaque has the exact synonym non-transparent and is relatedly synonymous with both clouding and cloudy.

Transparent is a type of opacity and is defined as an optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking opacity. Furthermore, transparent has exact synonyms, which include clear and hyaline.

Undulate is a type of shape characterized by a sinuate margin and a rippled surface, defining its quality. It is precisely synonymous with "undulated," "undulating," "waved," and "wavy." Additionally, it shares a related synonymy with "rippled" and "sinuate."

Permeability is a type of structure that is defined as a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid, such as by osmosis or diffusion.

Porosity is a type of structure that has a definition as a structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to admit the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

Permeable is a type of permeability and is disjoint with impermeable, indicating that something cannot be both permeable and impermeable at the same time. The definition of permeable is a permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid, as by osmosis or diffusion. Additionally, permeable is related to the synonym porous.

Impermeable is a type of permeability, defined as a permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being incapable of being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid, such as by osmosis or diffusion.

Porous is a type of porosity and it is distinct from non-porous. It is defined as a porosity quality that exists in an entity because the entity allows for the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

Non-porous is a type of porosity characterized by the quality of being incapable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices. This definition indicates that the property of non-porosity inherently belongs to a material due to its inability to allow the flow of substances through its structure.
Viscosity is a type of quality of a liquid, defined as a physical quality of a fluid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to internal resistance to flow.
Viscous is a type of viscosity, characterized by a viscosity quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's viscosity.

Physical quality is a type of physical object quality, defined as a quality of a physical entity that exists through the action of continuants at the physical level of organization in relation to other entities. It is also exactly synonymous with relational physical quality.

Mass density is a type of physical quality and is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass per unit size. Additionally, mass density is related to the synonym 'density'.
Momentum is a type of movement quality, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's velocity multiplied by its mass.
Pressure is a type of physical quality, defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of force per unit area it exerts.
Acceleration is a type of movement quality and is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the rate of change of the bearer's velocity in either speed or direction.
Efficiency is a type of physical quality and it is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the ratio of the bearer's output to the bearer's input.
Flux is a type of movement quality and is defined as a physical quality that exists by virtue of the rate of flow of the bearer across a given surface.
Elasticity is a type of physical quality, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.
Elongated is a type of shape that has the definition of a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably higher than its width.
Concentrated is a type of concentration, and it is defined as a concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting concentration.
Diluted is a type of concentration and is defined as a concentration which is relatively low.

Increased concentration is a type of concentrated and also falls under the category of increased object quality. It is defined as a concentration which is higher relative to the normal or average. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: high concentration.

Decreased concentration is a type of concentration as well as a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a concentration which is lower relative to the normal or average, and it also has an exact synonym: low concentration.
Dense is a type of mass density and it is defined as a physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting density.

Elastic is a type of elasticity and is disjoint with inelastic. It is defined as an elasticity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

Inelastic is a type of elasticity, characterized by an elasticity quality that inheres in a bearer. This quality is defined by the bearer's inability to recover its size and shape after any form of deformation.
Medial to is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's location toward the middle relative to another entity.

Lateral to is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that is inherent in a bearer due to the bearer's location toward the side relative to another entity. Furthermore, lateral to is exactly synonymous with lateral.
"Proximal to" is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's location being more central than another entity.
Linear is a type of shape that is defined by a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being narrow, with the two opposite margins parallel.
A Y-shaped is a type of tripartite, defined by a concave 3-D shape quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's form being shaped like the letter Y.
Odorless is a type of odor and it is defined as an odor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking odor.

A variant is a type of variability and it is defined as a variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits variation or change. Additionally, variant has an exact synonym: variable.
Strength is a type of physical quality and it is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's power or force.

Distal to is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that is inherent in an entity because it is located further from a more centrally located entity. This position is also exactly synonymous with the term "distal."

Process quality is a type of quality that is distinct from physical object quality. It is defined as a quality which inheres in a process. Furthermore, process quality is exactly synonymous with the quality of a process, quality of occurrent, quality of process, and relational quality of occurrent.

Physical object quality is a type of quality and it is defined as a quality which inheres in a continuant. This concept is exactly synonymous with several terms including monadic quality of a continuant, multiply inhering quality of a physical entity, quality of a continuant, quality of a single physical entity, quality of an object, and quality of continuant. Additionally, it has narrow synonyms such as monadic quality of an object and monadic quality of continuant.
Electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality is a type of radiation quality defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with electromagnetic radiation.

Full spectrum EM radiation quality, a type of quality pertaining to the interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation, is defined as an EM radiation quality that is independent of the EM wavelength range.

The radiation reflective quality, which is a type of full spectrum electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality, is defined as a scalar EM radiation quality obtained by the bearer's capacity to scatter or reflect radiation.
Albedo is a type of radiation reflective quality, defined as a reflective quality restricted to a particular wavelength.
Luminous flux is a type of optical quality defined as a scalar optical quality obtained by the magnitude of the light emitted by the bearer.

Optical quality is a type of electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality and also a type of quality concerning the interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation. Furthermore, optical quality is defined as an EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation falls within the specific range of the spectrum deemed to be visible light.

Variability is identified as a type of quality and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to varying or changing. It also has a related synonym, which is the variability of a physical quality.

Increased temperature is a type of temperature and also falls under the category of increased object quality. It is defined as a temperature that is relatively high, and it has exact synonyms such as "high temperature" and "hot."

Decreased temperature is a type of temperature and also a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a temperature which is relatively low. Moreover, decreased temperature has exact synonyms: cold and low temperature.

Duration is a type of physical quality of a process and it is defined as a process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending point. Additionally, duration has an exact synonym, which is "period," and a related synonym, "time."
Area is a type of 2D extent and it is defined as a 2D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two-dimensional extent.
Amorphous is a type of morphology that is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of distinct morphology.
Area density is a type of mass density and is defined as a density quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given area.
Volumetric density is a type of mass density, defined as a density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given volume.
Translucent is a type of opacity, characterized by an optical quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's low opacity.
Filamentous is a type of shape which is defined by a shape quality inhering in a bearer, due to the bearer's characteristic of having thin filamentous extensions at its edge.
Lobate is a type of surface feature shape that is defined by a surface feature shape quality which inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's deeply undulating edges forming lobes.
Striated is a type of shape, which is defined by a shape quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer being marked by narrow lines or grooves, typically parallel.
Structured is a type of structure and it is defined as a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a distinct structure.
Unstructured is a type of structure characterized by a structural quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's lack of distinct structure.

Angular velocity is a type of velocity defined as a physical quality inherent in a bearer by virtue of the rate of the bearer's angular movement about an axis, specifically referring to the angle rotated in a given time.
Buoyancy is a type of physical quality defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to rise or float in a fluid medium such as water or air.
Dead is a type of viability characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer due to the cessation of the bearer's life.
Medium acidity is a type of acidity that is defined as a concentration quality inhering in a medium due to the bearer's tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.
Acidic is a type of medium acidity, defined by an acidity quality inherent in a solution due to a high concentration of H+ ions.
Alkaline is a type of medium acidity characterized by an inherent quality in a solution due to the bearer's low concentration of H+ ions.
Decayed is a type of viability and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decomposition into component parts.
Attachment quality is a type of structure defined as a structural quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer having a connection or association with another entity.
Wholeness is a type of structure that is defined as a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer includes all its components.

Broken is a type of wholeness and is defined as a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's components no longer being in a single contiguous unit. It has an exact synonym, which is fragmented. Moreover, broken has a narrow synonym, fractured. Additionally, broken is relatedly synonymous with cracked, hemorrhaged, split, and torn.

Calcified is identified as a type of composition and is defined by the quality of composition that is characterized by the bearer being encrusted or impregnated with calcium carbonate (CHEBI:3311). Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with calcareous and narrowly synonymous with calcification.
"Detached from" is an attachment quality characterized by a bearer's lack of connection or association with another entity. This attachment quality is precisely synonymous with "detached."
Sensitivity to oxygen is a type of sensitivity toward which is defined as a sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's dependence on oxygen.

Aerobic sensitivity refers to a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's dependence on oxygen, indicating a type of sensitivity to oxygen. Aerobic is disjoint with anaerobic, meaning they are mutually exclusive.
Anaerobic sensitivity to oxygen is characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer, which stems from the bearer's independence on oxygen.
Decreased depth is a type of decreased size and also a type of depth. It is defined as a depth which is relatively low and has exact synonyms, including low depth and shallow.
An increased position is a type of position and also a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a position which is relatively high and has a related synonym, high position.

Decreased position is a type of position and also falls under the category of decreased object quality. It is defined as a positional attribute that is relatively low. Moreover, decreased position is synonymously related to low position.
Sloped is a type of shape, defined by the quality it inherits from having an oblique or slanted direction.

Condensed is a type of structure characterized by a structural quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer being thicker or more closely packed together, essentially being pressed tightly together. It is broadly synonymous with compact and has exact synonyms including compressed and squashed. Additionally, condensed is relatedly synonymous with dense.

Spherical is a type of spheroid and is defined as a spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a ball, specifically a sphere whose equatorial diameter is equal to the polar diameter. Additionally, spherical has the exact synonym "globular" and a related synonym "rotund."

Functionality is a type of physical object quality, characterized by the ability of a single physical entity to perform regular functions. This quality arises from whether the bearer exhibits the capability to do so.
Functional is a type of functionality, defined as a quality held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform a regular function(s).
Sound speed is a type of speed that is defined as a physical quality inhering in sound by virtue of the bearer's traveling speed in a given medium under specified conditions.
Solubility is a type of molecular quality characterized by the definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.
Flexibility is a type of quality of a solid, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

Flexible is a type of flexibility and is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking. Additionally, flexible has an exact synonym: bendy.

Inflexible is a type of flexibility, defined as a physical quality inherent in a bearer due to the bearer's inability to be turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking. It is exactly synonymous with "stiff" and is relatedly synonymous with "stiffness."

The quality of a solid is a type of quality of a substance and is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable. Additionally, the quality of a solid has an exact synonym: solidity.

Quality of a gas is a type of quality of a substance and it is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape. Additionally, quality of a gas has an exact synonym, gaseous.

The quality of a liquid is a type of quality of a substance. It is defined as a physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape. Additionally, the quality of a liquid has the exact synonym "liquidity."

Having extra function is identified as a type of functionality and is also considered a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a functionality quality possessed by an entity when it is capable of performing additional or different functions. Furthermore, having extra function is exactly synonymous with having supernumerary functions.

Decreased mass belongs to the category of mass and is also considered a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a mass which is lower than normal or average. Additionally, decreased mass is exactly synonymous with both low mass and small mass.

Increased mass is a type of mass and also a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a mass that is higher than normal or average. Moreover, increased mass has exact synonyms which are high mass and large mass.

Distributed is a type of spatial pattern and is disjoint with aggregated. It is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being spread out or scattered about or divided up. Additionally, distributed has the exact synonyms "diffuse" and "scattered."
Flow rate, a type of movement quality, is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer due to the characteristic of the bearer's motion.
Decreased pressure is a type of pressure and a type of decreased object quality, defined as a pressure which is relatively low. It is also exactly synonymous with low pressure.
Increased pressure is a type of pressure and is also a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a pressure which is relatively high and has an exact synonym: high pressure.
Decreased variability is a type of variant and is also considered a type of decreased quality. It is defined as a variability which is relatively low and has the exact synonym "low variability."
Increased variability is a type of variant and also a type of increased quality. It is defined as a variability which is relatively high and has an exact synonym, high variability.
Conductivity is a type of physical quality defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit an entity through a medium.
Curvature is a type of shape that is defined as a surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a degree of bending.
Arched is a type of concave and it is defined as a concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's forming or resembling an arch.
Depth is a type of 1-D extent and it is defined as a 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimension.
Increased depth is identified as a type of increased size and also as a type of depth. It is defined as a depth quality which is relatively high and has the exact synonym "deep."

Protruding is identified as a type of physical quality and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond a surface or boundary. Additionally, protruding is exactly synonymous with itself and also has an exact synonym, relational protruding quality.
Patchy is a type of irregular spatial pattern, defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by, consisting of, or diversified with patches.

Deformed is a type of morphology and is defined as a morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being distorted in form. Additionally, deformed is relatedly synonymous with disfigured and distorted.

Decreased functionality is categorized under both functional types and decreased object quality types. It is defined as a functionality quality possessed by the bearer, characterized by a reduced capability to perform one or more standard functions. In broader terms, decreased functionality is synonymously known as dysfunction and dysfunctional. It has exact synonyms including having decreased function, lacks function of type, low functionality, and partial functionality. Additionally, decreased functionality is relatedly synonymous with impaired.

Increased functionality is classified as a type of functional and also as a type of having an extra function. It is defined as a functional quality that is possessed by the bearer when there is an increased ability to perform regular functions. Furthermore, increased functionality is exactly synonymous with high functionality.

Aggregated refers to a type of irregular spatial pattern and is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being gathered or tending to gather into a mass or whole. Furthermore, aggregated is exactly synonymous with both "clumped" and "clustered."
Dispersed is a type of position, defined by a positional quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's distribution or spread over a considerable extent.

"Anterior to" is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's location toward the front of an organism relative to another entity. Additionally, "anterior to" is exactly synonymous with "preceding."

Protruding into is a type of protruding and is defined as a quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary into the surface or boundary of another entity.

Protruding out of is a type of protruding characterized by a quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's extension out above or beyond its surface or boundary and outwards in relation to the physical space occupied by another entity. It has an exact synonym, which is extruding from, and related synonyms, including exits through and exposed.
Circumference is a type of perimeter and it is defined as a one-dimensional extent quality, which equals the length of the closed curve of a circle.
Alignment is a type of position that possesses the definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity.

Aligned with is a type of alignment and it is defined as an alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in proper spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity. Additionally, aligned with has the exact synonym "aligned" and a related synonym "aligned to".

Misaligned with is a type of alignment and has the definition of being an alignment quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's improper spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity. Furthermore, it has the exact synonyms "misaligned" and "unaligned with."
Osmolarity is a type of concentration and is defined as a concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.
Increased osmolarity is a type of osmolarity and also a type of increased object quality. It is defined as an osmolarity which is relatively high and has an exact synonym: high osmolarity.

Increased distribution is a type of increased position and is also a type of distributed. It is defined as a distribution which is relatively high, and it has an exact synonym, which is high distribution.

Decreased distribution is a type of decreased position and is also a type of distributed. It is defined as a distribution which is relatively low. Moreover, decreased distribution has an exact synonym: low distribution.
Decreased efficiency is a type of efficiency and also a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as an efficiency which is relatively low, and it has an exact synonym: low efficiency.

Increased efficiency falls under the category of efficiency and is also considered a type of increased object quality. It is defined as an efficiency which is relatively high and has the exact synonym "high efficiency."
Efficient is a type of efficiency and it is defined as an efficiency quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having efficiency.
Magnetism is a type of physical quality, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to exert an attractive or repulsive force on other entities.
Magnetic is a type of magnetism and it is defined by a magnetic quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's ability to exert magnetism.
Elevation is a type of position and it is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.

Increased elevation is a type of elevation and also a type of increased position. It is defined as an elevation which is relatively high. Additionally, "high elevation" is an exact synonym, and "elevated" is a related synonym for increased elevation.

Decreased elevation is a type of elevation and also falls under the category of decreased position. It is defined as an elevation which is relatively low. Additionally, decreased elevation has an exact synonym, which is low elevation.

Increased viscosity is a type of viscous and also represents a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a viscosity which is relatively high. Moreover, increased viscosity has an exact synonym: high viscosity.
1-D extent is a type of size and is defined as a size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in one dimension. Furthermore, 1-D extent is exactly synonymous with 1-D size.

2D extent is a type of size and is defined as a size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions. Additionally, 2D extent has an exact synonym, which is "2-D size."
3D extent is a type of size and it is defined as a size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in three dimensions. Additionally, 3D extent has an exact synonym: 3D size.
Perimeter is a type of 1-D extent and is defined as a 1-D extent quality inhering in a two-dimensional bearer by virtue of being equal to the distance around it.
Increased perimeter, which is defined as a perimeter that is relatively high, falls under two categories: it is a type of increased length and also a type of perimeter.
A decreased perimeter, which is a type of perimeter and also a type of decreased length, is defined as a perimeter which is relatively low.
Shedability is a type of organismal quality, defined as an organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to lose an entity by natural process.
Deciduous, which is a type of shedability, is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to shed body parts.
A deciduous plant is characterized by the quality of shedding foliage, which is a type of sheddability. This quality inheres in a plant due to the bearer's disposition to shed its foliage.
Non deciduous any body part is a type of shedability, which is defined as a quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer's disposition to not shed any body part.
An evergreen plant is a type of shedability, characterized by a quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer's disposition to retain foliage.
A semi deciduous plant is a type of shedability and is defined by a quality inhering in a plant, by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being between evergreen and deciduous.

Radiation quality is a type of physical quality and also a type of something that is at least characteristic of something that is an intersection of a continuant and something that at least participates in some form of radiation. Moreover, radiation quality is defined as a quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

The activity of a radionuclide is a type of radiation quality as well as a type of quality of a substance. It is defined as a radiation quality that inheres in a radioactive substance due to its transformation (disintegration) rate. Additionally, the activity of a radionuclide has an exact synonym: radioactivity.
Radioactive, a type of activity of a radionuclide, is defined as a radiation quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer exhibiting or being caused by radioactivity.

Heat conductivity, which is a type of conductivity, is defined as a conductivity quality inherent in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to spontaneous transfer of thermal energy from a region of higher temperature to a region of lower temperature. Furthermore, heat conductivity has an exact synonym, thermal conduction.
Electrical conductivity is a type of conductivity defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to convey electricity.
Granular is a type of composition, defined by the quality of containing granules. This composition quality inheres in a bearer due to the presence of granules.
Decreased strength is a type of strength and also a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a strength which is relatively low and has an exact synonym, which is weak.
Irregular thickness is a type of thickness characterized by a quality that lacks pattern.

Increased mass density is a type of density as well as a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a density which is higher relative to the normal or average, and it has the exact synonym "high density."
Domed is a type of curved and it is defined as having a curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a shape resembling a dome.

Decreased mass density is a type of dense and also a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a density which is lower relative to the normal or average. Furthermore, decreased mass density has an exact synonym: low density.
Left side of is a type of position that has a definition as a spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located on the left side from another entity.
The "right side of" denotes a type of position with a definition that it is a spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located on the right side of another entity.
Coiling is a type of shape that has the definition of a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being wound in a continuous series of loops.
Ruffled is a type of shape, characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's exhibiting disturbance of its smoothness or regularity.
Wetness is a type of physical quality and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's being covered by a liquid.

Wet is a type of wetness and is disjoint with dry, meaning it does not share any common elements with dry. Moreover, wet has a definition as a wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered by a liquid.
Dry is a type of wetness and is defined as a wetness quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being covered by a liquid.
Increased wetness is both a type of wet and a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a wetness quality that is relatively high.
Decreased wetness is a subtype of both wet and decreased object quality. It is defined as a wetness quality that is relatively low and has an exact synonym "low wetness."
Decreased fluid flow is a type of fluid flow rate and a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a flow that is relatively low and has an exact synonym: low flow.
Increased fluid flow is a type of fluid flow rate and a type of increased object quality. It is defined as a fluid flow that is relatively high and has the exact synonym "high flow."

Acidity is a type of concentration and is defined as a concentration quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer containing acid (hydrogen ions). Additionally, acidity has an exact synonym: pH.
Increased acidity is a type of acidity and also falls under the category of increased object quality. It is defined as an acidity which is relatively high and has the exact synonym "high acidity."
Tangled is a type of structure that has a structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being entwined and difficult to unravel.
Vertical is a type of spatial pattern and it is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being situated at right angles to the horizon.

Horizontal is a type of position characterized by a positional quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's alignment with the plane of the horizon. This definition encapsulates the essence of being horizontal.
Concave is a type of concavity, characterized by a shape quality in a bearer due to the bearer's inward curving.

Spheroid is a type of convex 3D shape that possesses a specific quality defined by having a quadric surface in three dimensions, obtained by rotating an ellipse about one of its principal axes, which includes spheres and oblate/prolate spheroids. Additionally, spheroid has a related synonym: sphericality.

Cylindrical is characterized as a type of convex 3-D shape that is defined by the quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's exhibition of a consistently-sized round cross-section. It is precisely synonymous with being rod-like and rod-shaped. Additionally, cylindrical is narrowly synonymous with being tubulate.

U-shaped is characterized as a type of concave 3-D shape that inherently possesses the quality of being shaped in the form of the letter U. It is exactly synonymous with horseshoe-shaped and has a narrow synonym of horseshoe.

Hydrophobicity is a type of physical quality that is disjoint with hydrophilicity. It is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being water-repellent; it tends to repel and not absorb water.

Hydrophobic is a type of hydrophobicity, defined by a quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's lack of affinity for water. This involves a tendency to repel and not absorb water, as well as a resistance to dissolving in, mixing with, or being wetted by water.

Hydrophilicity is a type of physical quality characterized by a specific definition: it is a physical quality that exists in an entity due to the entity's tendency to have an affinity for water, meaning it readily absorbs or dissolves in water.

Hydrophilic is a type of hydrophilicity, defined by the quality inhering in a bearer, which is characterized by the bearer's disposition to having a strong affinity for water. This includes tendencies to dissolve in, mix with, or be wetted by water.

Tripartite is a type of branched and also a type of concave 3D shape. It is defined as a concave 3D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being divided into three branches. Furthermore, tripartite has an exact synonym, trifurcate.
Decreased circumference is both a type of circumference and a type of decreased perimeter with the definition: a circumference which is relatively low.

Front is a type of direction and it is defined as a directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the south when it faces north.

Back is identified as a type of direction and it is defined by a directional quality that exists in an entity because of the entity's orientation, specifically resembling the direction an object has towards the north when it is facing south.
Unidirectional is a type of direction characterized by a directional quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer having only one direction.
Bi-directional is a type of direction characterized by a directional quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's capability of having two directions.
Circling direction is a type of direction that is defined as a directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction approximating the shape of a circle.
Movement quality is a type of physical quality, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participation in movement.
Surface feature shape is a type of shape, which is defined as a surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape of features present on its surface or outer shell.
Opposite is a type of position that is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned on opposite sides on the same plane.

Obtuse is a type of circular shape and it is defined as a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, slightly inclining to be oblong. Moreover, obtuse has an exact synonym: roundish.
Variability of size, a type of variability, is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits size variation or change.

Decreased variability of size is identified as a type of variability of size and also as a type of decreased quality. It is defined as a variability of size which is relatively low, and it is exactly synonymous with low variability of size.

Increased variability of size is a type of variability of size and also a type of increased quality. It is defined as a variability of size which is relatively high and has the exact synonym "high variability of size."

Interdigitated is a type of shape and has the definition of a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's parts or projections being interlocked; for example, the fingers of two hands that are clasped.

Angular is a type of shape that has the definition of being a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having at least one salient angle on the margin. Additionally, angular has an exact synonym, angulate.
Frozen is a type of temperature, characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.
Dissolved is a type of solubility, and it is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's passing into solution.
Organismal quality is a type of physical object quality and is defined as a quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

Decreased amount is categorized as a type of present and also as a type of decreased quality. It is defined as an amount which is relatively low. Moreover, decreased amount is exactly synonymous with decreased number and present in fewer numbers in organism. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with decreased, reduced, and subnumerary.
Concavity is a type of shape that is defined by the surface shape, referring to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.

A 2D shape is a type of shape that is defined as a shape that inheres in a 2-dimensional entity, such as a cross section or projection of a 3-dimensional entity. Moreover, it has related synonyms including "2-D projection" and "cross-sectional."

A convex 3D shape is a type of 3D shape that is defined as a complete three-dimensional object in which every line connecting a pair of points on the object lies within the object. This means it is a shape that lacks cavities, in contrast to a concave shape.

A concave 3D shape is a type of 3D shape. It is defined as a complete three-dimensional shape in which there is a line connecting a pair of points on the object that lies outside the object, or simply, a shape with cavities. This is in contrast to convex shapes.
Branchiness is a type of shape, characterized by a shape quality that inheres in a bearer due to the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.
Structure cavities are a type of structure that is characterized by a structural quality. This quality inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's feature of containing hollow areas.

Conical is a type of convex 3D shape and has the definition of a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a cone, which is a 3D shape with a round cross section that tapers. Furthermore, conical is exactly synonymous with being cone-shaped.
Increased area is a type of increased size and also a type of area. It is defined as an area which is relatively high.
Decreased area is a type of decreased size and is also a type of area. It is defined as an area which is relatively low.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:physical_quality_of_a_process rdfs:subClassOf :process_quality .
text: physical quality of a process is a type of process quality.
Columnar is a type of shape that is defined as a shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being elongated and cylindrical.
Fenestrated is a type of structure characterized by a quality that inheres in it due to it being delimited by a surface with holes.
Stratification is a type of spatial pattern, which is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's layered configuration.
Stratified is a type of stratification and is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.
Hollow is identified as a type of structure characterized by cavities. It is defined by the quality that inheres in a bearer, attributed to the bearer's possession of an empty space or cavity within.
Being broken into two pieces is a type of brokenness, characterized by a broken quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's separation into two contiguous wholes.

Infiltrative is a type of structure characterized by a structural quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's capacity to penetrate or permeate another substance or area. Additionally, infiltrative is exactly synonymous with infiltrating.
Peripheral is a type of position and it is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being at the edge or boundary of a related entity.

Trabecular is a type of irregular spatial pattern and is defined as a spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's structure resembling an irregular meshwork with cross-linking struts.
Laminar is a type of structure that is characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate, sheet, or layer.

Edibility is a type of physical quality and is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being fit to be eaten. Additionally, edibility has an exact synonym: edibleness.

Edible is a type of edibility and is disjoint with inedible, meaning it cannot be both edible and inedible at the same time. Additionally, edible is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as food.
Inedible is a type of edibility and is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as food.
Irregular density is a type of mass density, characterized by a density quality that lacks pattern.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:sloped_downward rdfs:subClassOf :sloped .
text: sloped downward is a type of sloped.
Drooping is a type of shape defined as to bent or hang downwards and has the exact synonym "sagging."

Misaligned towards is a type of misaligned with and it is defined as an alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in an improper spatial positioning towards an additional entity.
Misaligned away from is a subtype of misaligned with, characterized by an alignment quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's improper spatial positioning away from another entity.
Straight is a type of shape that is defined by a shape quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer being free of curves, bends, or angles.
Displaced is a type of position and it is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being changed in position.

Molecular quality is a kind of physical object quality characterized by definition A quality that inheres in a molecular entity, such as a single molecule, atom, ion, or radical. Additionally, molecular quality is precisely synonymous with relational molecular quality.
The quality of a substance is a type of physical quality and it is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

Slender is a type of shape that is defined as a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being small or narrow in circumference or width in proportion to length or height. Additionally, slender has a related synonym, gracile.

Falciform is a type of shape characterized by a quality that inheres in a bearer because of the bearer's resemblance to the shape of a scythe or sickle. It is exactly synonymous with falcate, hooked, scythe-shaped, sickle-shaped, unciform, and uncinate.
Fan-shaped is a type of 2D shape that is characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer that is shaped in the form of a fan. Additionally, fan-shaped is exactly synonymous with fan-like.

V-shaped is a type of angular, and it is defined by an angular shape quality inherent in a bearer, by virtue of the bearer's having a single angle in its length, giving the bearer the form of the letter V.

Far from is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that inheres in a bearer because the bearer is located far away, not close to, in space in relation to another entity. Additionally, far from is exactly synonymous with both distant from and remote from.
Velocity is a type of movement quality, defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of position.

Fluid flow rate is a type of flow rate defined as a physical quality inhering in a fluid (liquid or gas) by virtue of the amount of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time. Additionally, fluid flow rate is exactly synonymous with both volume flow rate and volumetric flow rate.

Platelike is a type of flat and has the exact synonym plate-like. It is defined by a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

Flattened is a type of curvature and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's surface becoming more extended in a plane. Additionally, flattened is synonymously related to compressed.

Grooved is a type of texture characterized by the quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer's marking with one or more channels. This texture is also synonymously related to being channeled or creased.

Semi erect is a type of erect and is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being partially upright in position or posture. Additionally, semi erect has the exact synonym semi upright.
A 3D shape is a type of shape that has a definition: a shape that inheres in a 3-dimensional entity.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:edge_shape rdfs:subClassOf :shape .
text: edge shape is a type of shape.
Centered is a type of position characterized by a positional quality. This quality inheres in a bearer because the bearer is located in a position that is equidistant from edges.

Accumulation is a type of structure that is defined as a structural quality of the collection or massing of one physical object within another physical object. It is also related to the synonym "pooled."

Increased accumulation is a type of accumulation that is defined as an increased number of physical objects accumulated within another physical object, usually due to a failure to break down or remove these objects in a timely manner. Furthermore, increased accumulation is exactly synonymous with "accumulated."
Decreased accumulation is a type of accumulation that is defined as an accumulation which is relatively low.
Being parallel to is recognized as a type of position. It is defined by a spatial quality that exists in an entity because of the entity's location at a constant distance from another object.

Transient is a type of structure characterized by a structural quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's underlying structure being capable of change. It is also exactly synonymous with transient structure.
Tubular is a type of cylindrical and also a type of hollow, defined as a cylindrical shape that is hollow. Additionally, tubular has exact synonyms which include tube-like, tube-shaped, and tubulate.
Increased quality, defined as a quality that has a value increased compared to normal or average, is a type of deviation from normal.
Decreased quality is a type of deviation from normal, defined as a quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

Decreased process quality falls under the category of both process quality and decreased quality. It is defined as a quality of a process that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

Decreased object quality is a type of physical object quality and also falls under the category of decreased quality. It is defined as a quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

Increased process quality is a type of process quality and also falls under the category of increased quality. It is defined as a quality of a process that has a value that is increased compared to the normal or average.

Increased object quality falls under the category of both physical object quality and increased quality. It is defined as a quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.
Fimbriated is a type of shape defined by having a fringe or border of hairlike or fingerlike projections.

Superelliptic is a type of 2D shape that has a definition as a shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; it is a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos^2/rt, y = b.cos^2/rt. Additionally, superelliptic has an exact synonym which is Lamé curve.
Temporal distribution quality, a type of physical quality of a process, is defined as a temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation or reference process.

Tholiform is a type of shape characterized by a specific quality. This quality is defined by the shape's inherent nature of being dome-shaped, which is a feature that a bearer possesses by virtue of this particular form.
Basal to is a type of position characterized by a spatial quality that inheres in a bearer. This quality arises from the bearer's location towards the base of an organism relative to another entity.
Cauline is a type of position which is defined by a spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the stalk of an organism relative to another entity.
Herbaceous is a type of shedability, which is defined as a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's upper parts dying back to the rootstock at the end of the growing season.
Broad is a type of shape, characterized by a quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's width being notably higher than its length.
Fluctuating is a type of variant characterized by recurrent and often more or less cyclic alteration.

An anvil is a type of concave 3D shape and has a definition as a concave 3-D shape that inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape, which is wider at one end and narrow in the middle. Additionally, an anvil has an exact synonym: anvil-shaped.
Sunken is a type of elevation and it is defined as being flattened from above downward; it is below the normal level or the level of the surrounding parts.
Exposed is a type of position that is open to view or not covered by another entity.

A sculpted surface is a type of surface feature shape characterized by a topographically complex structure marked by large amounts of relief, often with multiple ridges and grooves in close association.

Abutting is a type of position characterized by a positional quality inhering in a bearer due to the bearer touching another entity along a border or with a projecting part. Additionally, abutting has an exact synonym which is "abut."
Offset is a type of position and it is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's position being displaced from a reference point.

Ornamentation is a type of surface feature shape and it is defined as a quality of a surface feature shape that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's high topographical characteristics, which include ridges, pits, rugosity, or other surface structures.
Ornamented is a type of ornamentation and it is defined as a surface feature shape where the bearer's surface is highly topographical, including ridges, pits, rugosity, or other surface structures.
Level with is a type of position and it is defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located at the same level as another entity.
Eroding is a type of structure that possesses a structural quality. This quality inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being gradually worn away.
"Extends to" is a type of position characterized by a positional quality that exists in a bearer because of some aspect of the bearer extending to the position of another entity.

Increased velocity is a type of velocity and also falls under the category of increased object quality. It is defined as a physical quality that inheres in a bearer due to the bearer's increased rate of change of position.

Decreased velocity is a type of velocity as well as a type of decreased object quality. It is defined as a physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decreased rate of change of the position.
External to is a type of position, characterized by the positional quality in which an entity is located outside of another entity.

Oblique to is a type of position characterized by a positional quality that inheres in a bearer. This is by virtue of the bearer's having a slanting direction, which is neither perpendicular nor parallel, relative to another entity.
Flush is a type of position, defined as a positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being level or even with another surface.
A funnel-shaped is a type of shape that has a definition as a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's similarity to the appearance of a funnel.

Variability of count is a type of variability characterized by a variability quality that inheres in the bearer. This quality is due to the bearer having a variable number or count of an entity. Additionally, variability of count is related to the synonym "variable number."
Radiating is identified as a shape category characterized by the quality of expanding outward or having parts that expand outward from a center point.

Continuous with is a type of position characterized by a positional quality that inheres in a bearer. This quality arises from the bearer possessing an uninterrupted or unbroken connection or spatial distribution relative to the position of another entity.

Disconnected is a type of structure that is characterized by a structural quality. This quality inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures that lack any physical connection to each other.
Humidity is a quality of a gas, defined as a quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer's water vapor content.
Increased humidity is a type of humidity and an increase in object quality. It is defined as an increase in humidity. Additionally, increased humidity is related to the synonym "humid."
Decreased humidity is classified as a type of humidity and represents a decrease in object quality. It is defined as a decrease in humidity.

Combustibility constitutes a type of physical quality, defined as the propensity of a material to undergo combustion, which includes both smouldering and flaming combustion. This characteristic is typically associated with solids.
Increased combustibility is a type of increased object quality and a type of combustibility. It is defined as an increase in combustibility and has an exact synonym, "combustible."

Plume-shaped is a type of shape defined as a shape that interests a bearer by virtue of the bearer's mass being distributed in a feather-like fashion. It also has exact synonyms: feather-shaped and plumed.

Fringed is a type of edge shape that is defined as a shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an ornamental border. This border consists of short straight or twisted threads or strips hanging from cut or raveled edges or from a separate band.
Bowl-shaped is a type of concave 3D shape, which has a definition as a concave 3D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of a bowl.
Normal object quality, a type of physical object quality, is defined as a quality of an object that has a value that is normal or average.
Normal position is a type of position and is characterized as a type of normal object quality. It is defined as a position which is relatively normal or average.
Normal pressure is both a type of pressure and a characteristic quality of a normal object. It is defined as a pressure that is relatively normal or average.
Normal size is a type of size and also a type of normal object quality. It is defined as a size quality which is relatively normal or average.
A normal area is a type of area and also a type of normal size. It is defined as an area which is relatively normal or average.
Normal depth is both a type of depth and a type of normal size. It has the definition of a depth quality which is relatively normal or average.
Normal volume is a type of volume and also a type of normal size. It is defined as a volume which is relatively normal or average.
Normal width is a type of width and also a type of normal size. It is defined as a width which is relatively normal or average.
Normal speed is a type of speed and also falls under the category of a normal object quality. It is defined as a speed which is relatively normal or average.
Normal velocity is a type of velocity and also a type of normal object quality. It is defined as a velocity which is relatively normal or average.

A cardinal direction is a specific type of direction. It is defined as the four cardinal directions or cardinal points, which are north, east, south, and west, frequently represented by their initials, N, E, S, W. Notably, east and west are positioned at right angles to north and south. East is situated in the clockwise direction of rotation from north, while west is located directly opposite east.
North is a type of cardinal direction and it is defined as one of the four compass points or cardinal directions. It is the opposite of south and is perpendicular to east and west.
East is a type of cardinal direction and is defined as one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass, being the opposite direction from west.
South is a type of cardinal direction and it is defined as one of the four cardinal directions or compass points. It is the polar opposite of north and is perpendicular to east and west.
West is a type of cardinal direction and it is defined as one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass, being the opposite direction from east.
Rate of occurrence is a type of rate that is defined as the number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series, such as the number of heartbeats occurring over 1 minute.
An increased rate of occurrence is a type of increased rate and also a type of rate of occurrence. It is defined as a rate of occurrence that is relatively high.
A decreased rate of occurrence is a specific type of decreased rate as well as a type of rate of occurrence. It is defined as a rate of occurrence that is relatively low.

The quality of interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation is a specific type of quality of a substance. It is defined as a quality of a substance on which or through which electromagnetic radiation impinges or traverses, concerning radiation. This particular substance quality alters the quality of the incident radiation in terms of intensity, direction, scatter, and wavelength.

A collection of organisms is a type of organismal entity that is defined as a material entity consisting of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids. This term can alternatively be referred to as a group of organisms or an organism collection. Examples of usage of the term "collection of organisms" include populations, communities, species (referring to the collection of organisms that constitutes a species, not the taxonomic rank), and families.

The population of organisms is classified as a type of caro 0001010, a type of single species collection of organisms, and a type that at least has some habitat. It serves as an example of usage, illustrating a general term that can encompass every organism of a species living in an area or any subset of them, with subclasses being more specific as needed. Moreover, it is defined as a collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

An ecological community, also known as a multispecies community, is defined as a collection of organisms that includes at least two different species. This multi-species collection of organisms lives in a particular area and must have at least two populations of different species as members.

A single species collection of organisms, also known as a collection of organisms of the same species, is a type of collection of organisms. It is defined as a material entity that comprises two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and includes no members of any other species.
A multi-species collection of organisms is a type of collection that is defined as a collection consisting of two or more organisms from at least two different species.
