An organismal entity is a type of material entity with the definition being a material entity that encompasses one or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

A multi-species collection of microbes, defined as a multi-species collection of organisms that consists of two or more microbes from at least two species, is a type of multi-species collection of organisms.

A microbial community is a type of ecological community and also a type of multi-species collection of microbes. It is defined as an ecological community which is composed of co-existing populations of microbial organisms that interact, directly or indirectly, such that they impact one another's ecological fitness. Additionally, the microbial community has a broad synonym: microbiota.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:whole_plant rdfs:subClassOf :plant_structure ;
    :has_broad_synonym "genet (broad)",
        "ramet (broad)" ;
    :has_definition "A plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism." ;
    :has_exact_synonym "planta entera (Spanish, exact)",
        "植物体全体 (Japanese, exact)" ;
    :has_narrow_synonym "bush (narrow)",
        "frutex (narrow)",
        "frutices (narrow)",
        "gametophyte (narrow)",
        "herb (narrow)",
        "liana (narrow)",
        "prothalli (narrow)",
        "prothallium (narrow)",
        "prothallus (narrow)",
        "seedling (narrow)",
        "shrub (narrow)",
        "sporophyte (narrow)",
        "suffrutex (narrow)",
        "suffrutices (narrow)",
        "tree (narrow)",
        "vine (narrow)",
        "woody clump (narrow)" ;
    :has_related_synonym "clonal colony (related)",
        "colony (related)" .
text: The whole plant is a type of plant structure, defined as a plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism. It has broad synonyms including genet and ramet. Exact synonyms for the whole plant are "planta entera" in Spanish and "植物体全体" in Japanese. The term also encompasses a wide range of narrow synonyms, indicating specific types or parts of a plant that fall under the broader category of the whole plant. These narrow synonyms include bush, frutex, frutices, gametophyte, herb, liana, prothalli, prothallium, prothallus, seedling, shrub, sporophyte, suffrutex, suffrutices, tree, vine, and woody clump. Additionally, the whole plant is related to concepts such as a clonal colony and colony, which are reflected as related synonyms.

The plant cuticle is a portion of plant substance that is adjacent to some epidermis. It is composed of cutin, a polyester matrix of hydroxy- and hydroxy epoxy fatty acids with C16 and C18 chains, embedded and overlaid with cuticular wax, and forms a layer on the surface of a plant epidermis. The plant cuticle has a broad synonym, "cuticle," and exact synonyms, including "cutícula" in Spanish and "植物クチクラ" in Japanese.

A shoot axis apex is a type of shoot axis and is defined as the most distal part of a shoot system (PO:0009006) that includes a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and the youngest primordia (PO:0025127). Additionally, the shoot axis apex has exact synonyms, including "ápice del epiblasto (epiblastema)" in Spanish and "シュート頂、茎頂" in Japanese.

The shoot axis epidermis is the same as an intersection of the shoot system epidermis and something that is at least part of a shoot axis. It is a type of shoot system epidermis and also a type of something that is at least part of a shoot axis. The shoot axis epidermis is defined as a portion of the shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035) that is part of a shoot axis (PO:0025029). Additionally, the shoot axis epidermis has exact synonyms including "epidermis del eje del tallo" in Spanish and "シュート軸表皮" in Japanese. It also has a narrow synonym, which is "branch epidermis."

The peripheral zone is a type of portion of meristem tissue and is part of at least some shoot apical meristem. It is defined as a portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) which serves as the organogenic region of the meristem, characterized by higher rates of cell division. The peripheral zone is also known by its exact synonyms "zona periférica" in Spanish and "周辺帯" in Japanese. Additionally, it has a related synonym, which is "peripheral meristem."

A meristematic cell is a type of native plant cell characterized by the synthesis of protoplasm and the production of new cells through division, possessing only a primary cell wall. This definition is recognized under the identifier PO:0025606. Additionally, meristematic cells have several exact synonyms across different languages, including "célula meristemática" in Spanish, "stem cell" in English, and "分裂組織細胞" in Japanese.

Root primordium is a type of primordium and also a type of entity that at least develops from some root anlagen. It is defined as a primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a root anlagen (PO:0025433) and is committed to the development of a root (PO:0009005). Additionally, root primordium has several exact synonyms including "portion of root primordium tissue," "primordio de raíz" in Spanish, "root primordia" in plural form, and "根原基（可視的）" in Japanese.

Epidermis is a type of plant tissue portion and something that develops from protoderm. It is defined as a portion of plant tissue composed of epidermal cells that originates from the protoderm and covers the surface of a plant structure. The epidermis has several exact synonyms, including dermal tissue, epidermal layer, epidermides, epidermis (in Spanish), epidermises, portion of epidermal tissue, and 表皮 (Japanese). Additionally, it has a related synonym, which is multiseriate epidermis.

Phyllome is a type of plant organ that is part of at least some shoot system and develops from some phyllome primordium. It is defined as a lateral plant organ (PO:0009008) produced by a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148). Additionally, phyllome has the exact synonyms "filoma" in Spanish and "フィロム、葉(的）器官" in Japanese.

The leaf epidermis is identified as being the same as an entity that intersects with the phyllome epidermis and something that constitutes at least a part of a leaf. It is categorized as a type of phyllome epidermis and also as a type of entity that is at least part of some leaf. The leaf epidermis is defined as a portion of the phyllome epidermis (PO:0025157) that is part of a leaf (PO:0025034). Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with several terms across languages: "epidermis de la hoja" in Spanish, "foliage leaf epidermis" in English, "phyllid epidermis" in English, and "葉表皮" in Japanese, all indicating the exact same concept.

The shoot system epidermis is identical to an entity that intersects with something that is an epidermis and also intersects with something that is at least part of some shoot system. It is classified as a type of epidermis and is also considered a type of entity that is at least part of some shoot system. Moreover, the shoot system epidermis is categorized as a type of entity that at least develops from some meristem L1 layer. The shoot system epidermis is defined as a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006) and arises from the meristem L1 layer (PO:0009020). Additionally, it has the exact synonyms "epidermis del epiblasto (epiblastema)" in Spanish and "シュート表皮" in Japanese.

The root epidermis is equivalent to an intersection of something that is an epidermis and something that is at least part of some root. It is classified both as a type of epidermis and as a type that is at least part of a root. Additionally, the root epidermis is defined as a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679) that is part of a root (PO:0009005). It has exact synonyms, including "epidermis de la raíz" in Spanish and "根表皮" in Japanese. Moreover, the root epidermis is relatedly referred to as epiblem and rhizodermis.

The shoot system meristem is a portion of meristem tissue that is part of a shoot system. It is defined as a portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that constitutes at least part of a shoot system (PO:0009006). Additionally, the shoot system meristem has exact synonyms including "meristema del epiblasto" (epiblastema) in Spanish and "シュート分裂組織" in Japanese.

Protoderm is a type of portion of meristem tissue, defined as a portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is the outer layer of an apical meristem (PO:0020144), or the outer layer of a plant embryo proper (PO:0000001), and gives rise to a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679). It has exact synonyms including "portion of protoderm tissue," "protodermis" in Spanish, and "前表皮、原表皮" in Japanese. Additionally, protoderm has a related synonym, which is "dermatogen cell."

The whole plant development stage is a type of plant structure development stage and also falls under the category of entities that involve whole plants as participants. It is defined as a plant structure development stage (PO:0009012) that primarily includes a whole plant (PO:0000003) as a participant. Additionally, the whole plant development stage is associated with several related synonyms, including Solanaceae whole plant growth stages (SGN:0000001), cereal plant growth stage ontology (GRO:0007199), maize growth stage (GRO:0007002), plant growth stages in Arabidopsis (TAIR:0000021), rice growth stage (GRO:0007040), sorghum growth stage (GRO:0007124), and wheat, barley, and oat growth stage (GRO:0007156).

A plant cell is a type of plant structure and is disjoint with a portion of plant tissue, a plant organ, and a collective plant organ structure. It is defined as a cell which is a plant structure (PO:0009011). Additionally, "plant cell" has a broad synonym "cell" and exact synonyms "célula vegetal" in Spanish and "植物細胞" in Japanese.

Root is identified as a type of plant axis, and it constitutes a part of at least some root system. Additionally, it develops from a root primordium. In terms of definition, a root is described as a plant axis (PO:0025004) that is devoid of shoot axis nodes (PO:0005004) and typically exhibits indeterminate growth. The term "root" is precisely synonymous with "raíz" in Spanish, "radices" in plural form, "radix," and "根" in Japanese. Furthermore, "aerial root" and "climbing root" are considered as narrow synonyms for root.

The shoot system is a type of collective plant organ structure, which is distinct from the root system. It is defined as a collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces shoot-borne portions of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) and the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them. The shoot system has exact synonyms, including "sistema de epiblasto (epiblastema)" in Spanish and "シュート系、苗条系" in Japanese. Additionally, it has a narrow synonym, "tree crown," and related synonyms such as "Poaceae crown," "shoot," "thalli," and "thallus."

A portion of plant tissue is identified as a type of plant structure and is distinctly separate from both plant organ and collective plant organ structure. It is defined as a plant structure (PO:0009011) that predominantly consists of similarly specialized plant cells (PO:0009002) of one or more types. This term is broadly synonymous with "portion of tissue" and "tissue." It has exact synonyms in other languages, including "porción de un tejido vegetal" in Spanish and "植物組織の一部" in Japanese. Additionally, "plant tissue" is considered a related synonym.

A plant organ is a type of multi-tissue plant structure, defined as a functional unit that is a proper part of a whole plant and includes portions of plant tissue of at least two different types that derive from a common developmental path. It is broadly synonymous with 'organ' and has exact synonyms in Spanish and Japanese, "&#243rgano vegetal" and "植物 器官" respectively. Additionally, related synonyms for plant organ include 'compound plant organ' and 'simple plant organ'.

Plant structure is a type of plant anatomical entity and is defined as a plant anatomical entity (PO:0025131) that is, or was, part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant. Additionally, "plant structure" has exact synonyms including "estructura vegetal" in Spanish and "植物 構造" in Japanese.

The plant structure development stage is a type of process and is defined as a stage in the life of a plant structure (PO:0009011) during which the plant structure undergoes developmental processes. This stage is exactly synonymous with "etapa de desarrollo de estructura vegetal" in Spanish and "plant growth and development stage." Additionally, it has a related synonym, which is "Arabidopsis growth."

A portion of meristem tissue is identified as a type of plant tissue and is also characterized as something that includes, at least in part, meristematic cells. It is defined as a portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) wherein plant cells (PO:0009002) have either retained their embryonic characteristics or have reverted to them secondarily. These cells divide to produce new cells capable of undergoing differentiation to form mature tissues, meaning they possess the capacity for morphogenesis and growth. The term "portion of meristem tissue" is precisely synonymous with "meristem," "meristema" in Spanish, "meristematic tissue," and "分裂組織" in Japanese, illustrating its exact equivalence across different languages.

The meristem L1 layer is a type of portion of meristem tissue and is also identified as part of a shoot apical meristem. It is defined as the outermost layer of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) that gives rise to a shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035). In terms of nomenclature, the meristem L1 layer has the exact synonyms "meristema L1" in Spanish and "分裂組織 L1" in Japanese. Additionally, it is relatedly referred to as "tunica".

Apical meristem is a type of portion of meristem tissue and is also something that at least has part of some protoderm. It is defined as a maximal portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) located at a shoot apex (PO:0000037) or root tip (PO:0000025). Furthermore, apical meristem is broadly synonymous with promeristem, and it has several exact synonyms including AM, meristema apical (in Spanish), and 頂端分裂組織 (in Japanese). Additionally, apical meristem is relatedly synonymous with primary meristem.

The shoot apical meristem is a type of meristem that belongs to both the shoot system meristem and apical meristem categories. It is also described as part of the apex of some shoot axis. The shoot apical meristem is defined as a shoot system meristem (PO:0006079) formed at the apex of the shoot axis (PO:0025029), including those originating from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232). In terms of nomenclature, the shoot apical meristem is broadly synonymous with promeristem and has exact synonyms such as SAM, meristema apical del epiblasto (epiblastema) in Spanish, and 茎頂分裂組織 in Japanese. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with primary shoot meristem.

Plant axis is a type of plant organ with the definition of an axial plant organ (PO:0009008). It has exact synonyms, including "eje de la planta" in Spanish, "plant axes" in plural form, and "植物軸（軸柱）" in Japanese.

A collective plant organ structure is a type of collective plant structure and also a type of structure that must include at least some part of a plant organ. It is defined as a collective plant structure (PO:0025497) that serves as a proper part of an entire plant (PO:0000003). This structure is characterized by comprising two or more adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) along with the associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007). Additionally, "collective plant organ structure" is exactly synonymous with "estructura vegetal colectiva de órgano" in Spanish and "集合植物器官構造" in Japanese.

The root system is a type of collective plant organ structure and is also a type of entity that at least participates in some sporophyte development stage. It is defined as a collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces root meristems (PO:0006085), the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them, and the parts thereof. Additionally, the root system has a broad synonym, which is "root," and exact synonyms, including "sistema de raíz" in Spanish and "根系" in Japanese.

Shoot axis is a type of plant axis and it is also a part of some shoot system. It is defined as a plant axis (PO:0025004) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006). The shoot axis has exact synonyms including caullome, eje del epiblasto (epiblastema) in Spanish, and シュート軸 in Japanese. Additionally, it has a related synonym, which is "shoot."
A leaf is a type of phyllome and is defined as a phyllome (PO:0006001) that is not associated with a reproductive structure. Moreover, it has the exact synonyms "hoja" in Spanish and "葉" in Japanese.

Primordium is a type of portion of meristem tissue with a definition as follows: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that includes protoderm (PO:0006210) and sub-epidermal meristematic tissue as its parts and is dedicated to the development of a specific plant structure (PO:0009011). Primordium is exactly synonymous with "portion of primordial tissue," "portion of primordium tissue," and "primordia" (the plural form). Additionally, it is precisely referred to as "primordio" in Spanish and as "原基（可視的）" in Japanese, both denoting the same concept.

Phyllome primordium is a type of primordium that is part of a shoot axis apex and develops from phyllome anlagen. It is defined as a primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) and is part of a shoot apex (PO:0000037), and it is committed to the development of a phyllome (PO:0006001). Moreover, phyllome primordium is exactly synonymous with "phyllome primordia," "portion of phyllome primordium tissue," "primordio del filoma" in Spanish, and "フィロム原基（可視的）" in Japanese.

A plant anatomical entity is a type of material entity and is also a type of something that at least RO 0002160 some viridiplantae. It is defined as an anatomical entity that is or was part of a plant. Furthermore, the exact synonyms for a plant anatomical entity include "entidad anatómica vegetal" in Spanish and "植物 解剖学（形態）的実体" in Japanese.

The phyllome epidermis is identified as being the same as an intersection between something that is part of the shoot system epidermis and something that is at least a part of a phyllome. It is classified as a type of shoot system epidermis and also as a type of entity that is at least part of a phyllome. The definition of phyllome epidermis is "A portion of shoot system epidermis (PO:0006035) that is part of a phyllome (PO:0006001)." Furthermore, it has the exact synonyms "epidermis del filoma" in Spanish and "フィロム表皮" in Japanese.

A portion of plant substance is categorized as a type of plant anatomical entity and is defined as a portion of organism substance that is or was part of a plant. Additionally, it has the exact synonyms "porción de sustancia vegetal" in Spanish and "植物を構成する物質の一部" in Japanese.

The life of the whole plant stage is a type of whole plant development stage, defined as a maximal whole plant development stage. It is exactly synonymous with "vida de la planta entera" in Spanish and "植物体の一生" in Japanese.

Cutin is a specific portion of plant substance, which constitutes at least part of some plant cuticles, including the plant cuticle proper. It is defined as the inner layer of a plant cuticle, composed of a polyester matrix of hydroxy- and hydroxy epoxy fatty acid C16 and C18 chains. Additionally, cutin is broadly synonymous with "cutin matrix" and has the exact synonym "クチン" in Japanese.

Cuticular wax is defined as a portion of plant substance (PO:0025161) comprised predominantly of very long chain aliphatic lipids and is part of a plant cuticle (PO:0000022). It is a type of substance that constitutes at least part of some plant cuticles. Furthermore, cuticular wax has the exact synonyms "cera cuticular" in Spanish and "クチクラワックス" in Japanese.

The plant cuticle proper is a type of portion of plant substance, defined as the inner layer of a plant cuticle, primarily composed of cutin, embedded, and overlaid with cuticular wax. It is broadly synonymous with both "cuticle proper" and "cutin matrix". Additionally, it has exact synonyms, including "cutícula propia de la planta" in Spanish and "植物クチクラproper" in Japanese.

Phyllome anlagen is a portion of meristem tissue and is part of some peripheral zone, specifically, it is defined as a portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148), and it will give rise to a phyllome primordium (PO:0025128). Additionally, phyllome anlagen has a broad synonym known as phyllome meristem and an exact synonym, which is フィロム原基 in Japanese.

Root anlagen is a type of portion of meristem tissue and is defined as a portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is committed to the development of a root primordium (PO:0005029). It is exactly synonymous with "precursor de raíz" in Spanish and "根原基" in Japanese.

Multi tissue plant structure is a type of plant structure defined as a plant structure (PO:0009011) that consists of two or more portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types. It forms a single structural unit through specific morphogenetic processes, demarcated by primarily bona-fide boundaries from other structural units of different types. Additionally, "multi tissue plant structure" has exact synonyms, including "estructura vegetal con múltiples tejidos" in Spanish and "複数の組織からなる植物構造" in Japanese.

Collective plant structure is a type of plant structure that is defined as a plant structure (PO:0009011) which is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003). It includes two or more adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) or adjacent cardinal organ parts (PO:0025001), along with any associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007). Additionally, the term "collective plant structure" has exact synonyms in other languages, including "estructura vegetal colectiva" in Spanish and "集合的植物構造" in Japanese.

Plant sap is defined as a portion of plant substance (PO:0025161) that is an aqueous solution capable of being transported through the apoplast (GO:0048046) or symplast (GO:0055044), and it is a type of portion of plant substance. Additionally, "savia de la planta" in Spanish and "植物液" in Japanese are its exact synonyms.

Plant resin is a type of portion of plant substance, specifically defined as a portion of plant substance (PO:0025161) that consists of a complex mixture of organic aromatic compounds such as mono-, sesqui-, and diterpenoids. It is exactly synonymous with pitch and is also relatedly synonymous with oleoresin.

A native plant cell is a specific type of plant cell. It is defined as a plant cell (PO:0009002) that is either a component of a multicellular whole plant (PO:0000003) 'in vivo' or a unicellular organism 'in natura' (meaning, as part of a natural environment).

The sporophyte development stage is characterized as a type of whole plant development stage and is also considered a part of some life of the whole plant stage. It is defined as a whole plant development stage (PO:0007033) that primarily involves a whole plant (PO:0000003) during the period from fertilization (or apogamy) to death. This stage is known by several exact synonyms, including "fase esporofítica" in Spanish, "sporophytic development stage," "sporophytic phase," "sporphyte phase," and the Japanese term "胞子体発生過程."
A system is a type of material entity defined as a material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.

The peripheral nervous system is a subdivision of the organ system and is part of the broader nervous system. It is defined as a major division of the nervous system that contains nerves which connect the central nervous system (CNS) with sensory organs, other organs, muscles, blood vessels, and glands. Moreover, it is broadly synonymous with PNS and has exact synonyms, including pars peripherica and systema nervosum periphericum.

The zone of skin is classified as a type of caro 0000000, ectoderm-derived structure, zone of organ, and something that constitutes at least a part of some skin of the body, including parts of the skin epidermis and dermis. It is defined as any portion of the organ that covers the body and consists of a layer of epidermis and a layer of dermis. Furthermore, the zone of skin is synonymously referred to as a portion of skin, region of skin, skin, skin region, and skin zone.

The camera type eye is a multifaceted structure with various classifications and associations. It is identified as a type of caro 0000000, simple eye, and ectoderm-derived structure, emphasizing its biological complexity. Additionally, it is characterized as a type of structure that benefits from developmental contributions from the neural crest, further highlighting its intricate development process. This eye is also acknowledged as a lateral structure and is associated with the orbital region, indicating its positional relevance in anatomical terms. Furthermore, it encompasses parts such as some lens of camera type eye and retina, and it develops from the optic cup, detailing its compositional and developmental specifics.

In terms of nomenclature, the camera type eye is defined as an organ of sight that incorporates the camera-type eyeball along with supporting structures like the lacrimal apparatus, the conjunctiva, and the eyelid. This definition encapsulates the eye's functional and structural breadth. The terminology surrounding the camera type eye is rich, with "eye" being a broad synonym, while "regio orbitalis" serves as an exact synonym. "Vertebrate eye" is considered a narrow synonym, illustrating the specificity within its categorization. Related synonyms include "camera-type eye plus associated structures," "eyes," "orbital part of face," and "orbital region," which collectively underscore the eye's significance in both anatomical and functional contexts.

A sense organ is a type of organ and also a type of entity that constitutes at least part of a sensory system. It is defined as an organ that is capable of transducing sensory stimuli to the nervous system. The sense organ has several exact synonyms, including organ of the sense organ system, organ of the sensory organ system, organ of the sensory system, sense organ system organ, sensory organ, sensory organ system organ, and sensory system organ. Additionally, it has a narrow synonym, sensillum, and related synonyms such as Sinnesorgan and sensor.

A cutaneous appendage is a type of integumentary projection, defined as an anatomical projection that protrudes from the skin, with examples including hair, nail, feather, claw, hoof, horn, wattle, spur, beak, antler, bristle, and some scales. It is also exactly synonymous with "skin appendage" and narrowly synonymous with "epidermal appendage." Additionally, it has a related synonym, "epidermal growth."

A feather is a type of cutaneous appendage, ectoderm-derived structure, and something that at least develops from some skin epidermis. It is defined as one of the epidermal growths that form the distinctive outer covering, or plumage, on birds. Feathers are formed in tiny follicles in the epidermis, or outer skin layer, that produce keratin proteins.

A tube is a type of anatomical conduit and also a type of something that at least has part some subdivision of a tube. It is defined as any hollow cylindrical anatomical structure containing a lumen through which substances are transported. Additionally, "anatomical tube" is an exact synonym for tube, and "duct" is considered a narrow synonym.

The head is a type of subdivision of an organism along the main body axis and is also considered at least part of the craniocervical region. It is defined as the anterior-most division of the body [GO]. Additionally, the head is exactly synonymous with the term "head (volume)" and has a narrow synonym "adult head." Furthermore, it is relatedly synonymous with the "cephalic area."
A simple eye is a type of eye characterized by having one concave chamber. It's important to note that the term 'simple' does not suggest a diminished level of complexity or acuity.
A vessel is an anatomical conduit type with the definition of being a tubular structure that contains and conveys body fluid, such as blood or lymph.

An anatomical wall is categorized as a type of organ part and also as a type of entity that possesses at least one organ component layer as a part. It is defined as an organ component adjacent to an organ cavity, consisting of a maximal aggregate of organ component layers. Additionally, "anatomical wall" is broadly synonymous with "wall," exactly synonymous with "wall of organ," and has a related synonym "organ wall."

An anatomical structure is a type of material anatomical entity that is defined as a material anatomical entity which is a single connected structure with an inherent 3D shape generated by the coordinated expression of the organism's own genome. Furthermore, "anatomical structure" has the exact synonyms "biological structure" and "connected biological structure."

An organ is a type of multicellular anatomical structure and is considered a part of at least one anatomical system. It is distinct from a multi-organ part structure. The definition of an organ is an anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions, as noted in Wikipedia (WP). Moreover, it is synonymously related to terms such as anatomical unit, body organ, and element.

An organ subunit is a type of organ part and is defined as a part of an organ that constitutes a distinct modular sub-unit. In some instances, the organ may contain other sub-units of identical or similar types, while in other instances, this may be a distinct entity. Additionally, an organ subunit is synonymously related to an organ region with a fixed fiat boundary, an organ segment, and a segment of organ.

Organ part is a type of multicellular anatomical structure and is also considered a type of something that is at least part of some organ. It is defined as a multicellular structure that is a part of an organ. Additionally, organ part is exactly synonymous with cardinal organ part and is relatedly synonymous with the regional part of an organ.

The regional part of the nervous system is identical to an entity that is both a multi-tissue structure and at least a part of some nervous system. It is categorized as a type of multi-tissue structure and also as a type that constitutes at least part of some nervous system. Furthermore, the regional part of the nervous system is defined as any part or collection of parts of the central or peripheral nervous system, with parts potentially spanning both the CNS (Central Nervous System) and the PNS (Peripheral Nervous System). Additionally, it is precisely synonymous with the term "part of nervous system."

A subdivision of the skeletal system is categorized as a type of organ system subdivision, and it is also considered a part of the skeletal system. Additionally, it is recognized as being comprised of or having parts that include skeletal elements. This subdivision is defined as an anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements and articular elements that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism. It is exactly synonymous with "skeletal system subdivision" and is relatedly referred to as a "skeletal system part."

The external ectoderm is a type of unilaminar epithelium, embryonic tissue, and part of some ectoderm. It is defined as the surface (external) layer of ectoderm which begins to proliferate shortly after separation from the neuroectoderm. Additionally, the external ectoderm is exactly synonymous with both surface (external) ectoderm and surface ectoderm.

A mixed endoderm mesoderm derived structure is an anatomical structure that develops from both the endoderm and the mesoderm. It is defined as an anatomical structure that intersects with structures that at least develop from some endoderm and structures that at least develop from some mesoderm. Additionally, a mixed endoderm mesoderm derived structure is classified as a type of both endoderm derived structure and mesoderm derived structure.

A mixed ectoderm, mesoderm, and endoderm derived structure is defined as an anatomical structure that develops from the ectoderm, mesoderm, and endoderm. This type of structure is equivalent to something that is at the intersection of an anatomical structure and something that at least develops from some ectoderm, something that at least develops from some endoderm, and something that at least develops from some mesoderm. Additionally, a mixed ectoderm, mesoderm, and endoderm derived structure is categorized as a type of mixed endoderm and mesoderm derived structure, as well as a type of ectoderm derived structure.

A neuron projection bundle is a type of multi-cell part structure and also a type that is at least part of some nervous system. It is defined as a fasciculated bundle of neuron projections (GO:0043005), largely or completely lacking synapses. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms including funiculus, nerve fiber bundle, and neural fiber bundle.

Neural nucleus is a type of caro 0000000, a type of central nervous system cell part cluster, and a type of something that at least has part some gray matter. It has a definition as a spatially aggregated collection of nerve cell bodies in the CNS, consisting of one or more subpopulations that share cell type, chemical phenotype, and connections, including nearby cells that share the same cell type, chemical phenotype, and connections (CUMBO). Neural nucleus has a broad synonym, nucleus, and exact synonyms including nervous system nucleus, neuraxis nucleus, neuronal nucleus, and nucleus of CNS. Additionally, it has a related synonym, nucleus of neuraxis.

:anterior_region_of_body rdfs:subClassOf :organism_subdivision .
text: anterior region of body is a type of organism subdivision.

The intestine is a type of subdivision of the digestive tract and is also considered a part of the alimentary portion of the gastrointestinal system. It is defined as a segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the anus, which, in humans and other mammals, consists of two segments: the small intestine and the large intestine. Furthermore, the intestine is exactly synonymous with the term "bowel" and is also relatedly referred to as the "intestinal tract."

An orifice is a type of anatomical conduit, defined as an anatomical conduit that connects two adjacent body spaces or a body space with the space surrounding the organism, as modified from FMA. It has broad synonyms including anatomical ostium and ostium, an exact synonym being anatomical orifice, and a narrow synonym hilum.

Cloaca is a type of subdivision of a tube that forms part of the digestive tract and the genitourinary system in some cases. It is defined as a common chamber into which the intestines and excretory system opens. This structure arises during development in all vertebrates, but in many cases, it becomes subdivided, lost, or incorporated into other structures. Additionally, cloaca is related to the terms "cloacal chamber" and "vent" as synonyms.

The embryonic cloaca is a type of cloaca that is part of an embryo, specifically forming part of the renal system and the internal anal region. It is defined as an endoderm-lined chamber that develops as a pouch-like dilation at the caudal end of the hindgut. It receives the allantois ventrally and two mesonephric ducts laterally. Caudally, it ends blindly at the cloacal membrane, which is formed by the union of proctodeal (anal pit) ectoderm and cloacal endoderm, with no intervening mesoderm. Additionally, the embryonic cloaca is also related to the term "cloaca."

The primitive urogenital sinus is a type of embryonic structure that is part of the embryonic cloaca and develops from the intermediate mesoderm. It is defined as the ventral part of the cloaca remaining after the septation of the rectum, which further develops into part of the bladder, part of the prostatic part of the male urethra, and the urethra and vestibule in females. The primitive urogenital sinus is broadly synonymous with the urogenital sinus and has exact synonyms including UGS, fetal UGS, and sinus urogenitalis.

The mouth is recognized as a subdivision of the digestive tract and is considered a part of the head, at least partially. It develops from what is known as the future mouth. The definition provided for the mouth is: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, it extends to the pharynx and encompasses the gums, lips, tongue, and parts of the palate. Usually, it also includes the teeth, except where these are located elsewhere (e.g., pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (such as tusks). The mouth is also referred to by several synonyms. The exact synonym is "regio oralis." It has narrow synonyms, such as "adult mouth." Related synonyms include "cavital oralis," "cavitas oris," "cavum oris," "mouth cavity," "oral region," "oral vestibule," "rima oris," "stoma," "stomatodaeum," "trophic apparatus," "vestibule of mouth," and "vestibulum oris."

The oral opening is a type of orifice and also a type of something that is at least part of some mouth. It is defined as the orifice that connects the mouth to the exterior of the body. The oral opening has exact synonyms such as oral fissure and oral orifice. Additionally, it has related synonyms like mouth and oral part of face.

Vomit, also known as vomitus, is a type of regurgitated substance. It is defined as a bodily fluid consisting of the expulsed contents of the stomach disgorged through the mouth or nose that happens as a result of a vomit reflex.

Amniotic fluid is a type of organism substance known by synonyms such as acqua amnii and liquor amnii. It is defined as a bodily fluid consisting of a watery liquid that surrounds and cushions a growing fetus within the amnion. This fluid facilitates the fetus's free movement, preventing the uterus walls from being too tight against its body and providing buoyancy. The composition of amniotic fluid evolves throughout gestation; it initially resembles maternal plasma, predominantly water with electrolytes. As gestation progresses, proteins, carbohydrates, lipids, phospholipids from the lungs, fetal cells, and urea accumulate in the fluid.

Excreta is a type of organism substance defined as a portion of organism substance that is the product of an excretion process, which will be eliminated from the body. This excretion process involves the elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity. Excreta is exactly synonymous with excreted substance, portion of excreted substance, and waste substance. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with excretion.

Pleural effusion is a type of pleural fluid, defined as a bodily fluid that is produced in excess and accumulates in the pleural cavity. This fluid-filled space surrounds the lungs, and excessive amounts of such fluid can impair breathing by limiting the expansion of the lungs during inhalation.
Oro-nasal secretion is a type of organism substance and is defined as a bodily fluid secreted from the body via the mouth or nose. It also has a narrow synonym, oronasal discharge.

Pus is a type of organism substance with the definition that it is a bodily fluid consisting of a whitish-yellow or yellow substance produced during inflammatory responses of the body. It can be found in regions of pyogenic bacterial infections and is produced from the dead and living cells that travel into the intercellular spaces around the affected cells. Additionally, pus is related to the synonym "purulent exudate."

Blood is a type of haemolymphatic fluid and is part of some hematopoietic systems. It is composed of blood plasma and develops from presumptive blood, undergoing an immediate transformation from presumptive blood. Blood is defined as a fluid composed of blood plasma and erythrocytes. It has exact synonyms such as "portion of blood" and "vertebrate blood," and a related synonym, "whole blood."

Haemolymphatic fluid is identified as a type of bodily fluid that is also categorized as a part of the hemolymphoid system. It is equivalent to the intersection of organism substance and a component of the hemolymphoid system. Moreover, it is defined as a circulating fluid that is part of the hemolymphoid system, including blood, lymph, interstitial fluid, or its analogs. Additionally, haemolymphatic fluid has related synonyms such as blood or blood analog, and circulating fluid.

A blastula is a type of embryo and is also a type of entity that develops from a cleaving embryo. It is defined as an organism at the blastula stage, which is an early stage of embryonic development in animals. This stage is produced by the cleavage of a fertilized ovum and consists of a spherical layer of around 128 cells surrounding a central fluid-filled cavity called the blastocoel. The development sequence of a blastula follows the morula and precedes the gastrula. Additionally, blastula has the exact synonym "blastula embryo" and is relatedly known as a blastosphere.

Late embryo is a type of embryo that is at the late embryonic stage. This stage covers the late steps of embryogenesis with a fully formed embryo still developing before birth or egg hatching. Moreover, late embryo has a narrow synonym "fetus" and related synonyms which include "embryo late growth stage" and "embryo late stage."

The gut wall is the same as something that is an intersection of an anatomical wall and something that is at least part of some digestive tract. It is defined as the wall of the digestive tract, which encompasses all parts of the digestive tract with the exception of the lumen (cavity). The gut wall is identified as a type of anatomical wall and also as a type of something that is at least part of some digestive tract. It has exact synonyms including digestive tract wall, wall of digestive tract, and wall of gut. Additionally, the gut wall has a related synonym, which is the wall of the alimentary tract.

Mucosa is recognized as a type of organ component layer that essentially comprises at least some part of epithelium and connective tissue. It is defined as a lining primarily of endodermal origin, which is covered in epithelium and plays a crucial role in absorption and secretion. Mucosa lines various body cavities exposed to the external environment and internal organs, often being continuous with the skin at specific points such as the nostrils, lips, ears, genital area, and anus. The term mucous membrane, another designation for mucosa, refers to its location in the body, noting that not every mucous membrane secretes mucus, which is a sticky, thick fluid produced by the mucous membranes and gland. Additionally, mucosa is also known by exact synonyms including mucosa of organ, mucosa of organ part, mucosal region, mucous membrane, and organ mucosa. It has related synonyms like region of mucosa and tunica mucosa, indicating the varied nomenclature used to describe this anatomical structure.

The limbic system is a type of organ system subdivision that is derived from the ectoderm. It is part of the forebrain to some extent. The limbic system encompasses a set of midline structures surrounding the brainstem of the mammalian brain, which includes the hippocampal formation, amygdala, hypothalamus, cingulate cortex. Originally described based on its anatomy, the limbic system is now associated with the brain's system subserving emotional functions, making its definition more complex and not closely aligned with its anatomical roots. Furthermore, it is also known by the related synonym "visceral brain."

The musculature of the body is identified as a type of caro 0000000, a type of organ system subdivision, and also as a type of entity that at least has part some musculature. It is defined as the subdivision of the musculoskeletal system that consists of all the muscles of the body, as modified from VSAO. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with several terms: muscle system, muscle system of body, muscular system, musculature system, set of all muscles, set of muscles of body, and vertebrate muscular system. Additionally, it has a related synonym: muskelsystem.

The secretion of an exocrine gland is a type of organism substance characterized by its production by exocrine glands. It is defined as a portion of organism substance that is produced by exocrine glands. This secretion is broadly synonymous with "secretion" and has exact synonyms including "bodily secretion," "exocrine gland fluid/secretion," and "secreted substance." Additionally, it has related synonyms such as "exocrine gland fluid," "exocrine gland fluid or secretion," "exocrine gland secretion," and "external secretion."

Organism substance is classified as a type of material anatomical entity and also falls into the category of things that are at least partially part of some multicellular organism. It is defined as a material anatomical entity in various states such as gaseous, liquid, semisolid, or solid, which is produced by anatomical structures or derived from substances that are inhaled or ingested and then modified by anatomical structures as they traverse through the body. Furthermore, organism substance is synonymously referred to as body fluid or substance, body substance, and portion of body substance or portion of organism substance.

An anatomical space is a type of immaterial anatomical entity, defined as a non-material anatomical entity of three dimensions, generated by morphogenetic or other physiological processes, surrounded by one or more anatomical structures, and contains one or more organism substances or anatomical structures. It has broad synonyms including "lumen" and "space," an exact synonym "lumen space," and a related synonym "anatomical spaces."

A material anatomical entity is both a type of material entity and a type of anatomical entity. It is disjoint with an immaterial anatomical entity. Furthermore, a material anatomical entity is defined as an anatomical entity that has mass.
An immaterial anatomical entity is a type of anatomical entity that has no mass and is exactly synonymous with immaterial physical anatomical entity.

An anatomical system is a type of anatomical structure, which is also a type of something that is at least part of some multicellular organism and a type of something that at least has some organ as part. It is defined as a multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts, and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function. The term "anatomical system" has a broad synonym "system" and exact synonyms including "body system," "connected anatomical system," and "organ system." Additionally, it has a related synonym "anatomical systems."

A multicellular organism is a type of multicellular anatomical structure defined as an anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of more than one cell. It is broadly synonymous with "organism" and exactly synonymous with "multi-cellular organism." Additionally, related synonyms for a multicellular organism include "Koerper," "body," "whole body," and "whole organism."

An organism subdivision is a type of multicellular anatomical structure and also a type of entity that constitutes at least part of a multicellular organism. It is defined as an anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems, largely surrounded by a contiguous region of integument. Furthermore, the term "organism subdivision" is exactly synonymous with "anatomic region" and is relatedly synonymous with "body part," "body region," and "cardinal body part."

An acellular anatomical structure is a type of anatomical structure that is distinctly separate from multicellular anatomical structures. It is defined as an anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances, which together do not constitute a cell or a tissue. Additionally, "acellular anatomical structures" is a related synonym for an acellular anatomical structure.
An anatomical cluster is a type of disconnected anatomical group, defined as an anatomical group that has its parts adjacent to one another.

An extraembryonic structure is defined as a multicellular anatomical structure associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis. It is synonymous with extra-embryonic structure and has related synonyms including extraembryonic structures and extraembryonic tissue. This type of structure is both a kind of developing anatomical structure and a type of entity that is at least part of an entire extraembryonic component. Additionally, an extraembryonic structure is the same as something that intersects with a developing anatomical structure and something that is at least part of an entire extraembryonic component.

Tissue is a type of multicellular anatomical structure and is part of some multicellular organism. It is defined as a multicellular anatomical structure consisting of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organization is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organization. Additionally, tissue is exactly synonymized with "portion of tissue" and "tissue portion," and has a narrow synonym, "simple tissue."
